# Files Railway doesn't need at build/runtime.
# Reduces the snapshot size sent to the Metal builder and the resulting image.

# Heavy ingestion-only artifacts; runtime reads chunks from cloud Supabase
# (knowledge_base/ stays — code references it for form_guides + the
# additive-intake GUI; size is moderate at 40MB; safer than discovering
# a runtime import the hard way like with tracers_and_logs/.)
artifacts/_archive/
artifacts/temp/
artifacts/_backup_*/
artifacts/query_embedding_cache/

# Eval + probe history (forensic record in git, not needed by the running server)
evals/
sme_panel_runs/
probe_runs/

# tracers_and_logs/ is a Python package imported by pipeline_d/orchestrator.py
# (pipeline_trace.py). The package code MUST ship; only the heavy logs/
# subdirectory is excluded.
tracers_and_logs/logs/
tracers_and_logs/__pycache__/

# Local dev scaffolding
supabase/.temp/
supabase/seed.sql
.venv/
node_modules/
frontend/node_modules/
frontend/dist/
ui/

# Tests don't run at deploy time
tests/

# Developer tooling
.claude/
.cursor/
.vscode/
*.log
*.pid
*.pyc
__pycache__/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/

# Docs we don't need on the running container
docs/
*.md
!README.md
# Re-include the interpretative_guidance corpus (105 .md files under
# knowledge_base/**/EXPERTOS/) — runtime data for the Interpretación de
# Expertos panel, read by src/lia_graph/interpretacion/catalog.py. Without
# this whitelist, the *.md glob strips the entire expert corpus and the
# panel renders empty in production while the chat (Supabase-backed) works.
!knowledge_base/**/*.md
